# Rails Boost — AI Instructions

This project uses Rails Boost. The MCP server is mounted at <%= mount_path %>/mcp.

## Stack
<% if stack.dig(:rails, :version) -%>
- Rails <%= stack[:rails][:version] %>, Ruby <%= stack.dig(:ruby, :version) || RUBY_VERSION %><% if stack.dig(:database, :adapter) %>, <%= stack[:database][:adapter] %><% end %>
<% end -%>
<% if stack[:test].any? -%>
- Test: <%= stack[:test].map { |t| t[:key] }.join(", ") %>
<% end -%>
<% if stack[:jobs].any? -%>
- Jobs: <%= stack[:jobs].map { |t| t[:key] }.join(", ") %>
<% end -%>
<% if stack[:frontend].any? -%>
- Frontend: <%= stack[:frontend].map { |t| t[:key] }.join(", ") %>
<% end -%>
<% if stack[:auth].any? -%>
- Auth: <%= stack[:auth].map { |t| t[:key] }.join(", ") %>
<% end -%>
<% if stack[:authz].any? -%>
- Authz: <%= stack[:authz].map { |t| t[:key] }.join(", ") %>
<% end -%>

## Active architecture skills
<% selected_arch_skills.each do |name| -%>
- @.claude/skills/<%= name %>/SKILL.md
<% end -%>

<% if discovered_gem_skills.any? -%>
## Installed gem skills
<% discovered_gem_skills.each do |skill| -%>
- @.claude/skills/<%= skill.name %>/SKILL.md   (source: <%= skill.gem %> <%= skill.spec_version %>)
<% end -%>
<% end -%>

## How to use the MCP tools
Prefer `run_ruby` for inspecting live state.
Use `run_sql` for read-only DB queries (SELECT/WITH/EXPLAIN/SHOW only).
Use `locate_source` to find where things are defined before guessing.
Use `list_models` and `list_routes` to map the app instead of grepping.
